04/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The main rightist opposition party, the Union of Democratic Forces (UDF), is inviting more than ten formations from the right-wing bloc to talks next month, UDF leader Nadezhda Michailova announced on Sunday (3 October). 
UDF is working to unite right-wing groups prior to the 2005 parliamentary elections. 
Michailova did not disclose which parties would be invited to the event. 
(Sega, Mediapool - 04/10/04)
